            <p><strong><a href="https://onward.justia.com/2016/10/28/california-bar-client-information-available-public-sources-still-confidential/" target="_blank">California Bar: Client Information Available from Public Sources is Still Confidential</a></strong></p>
            <p>The State Bar of California Standing Committee on Professional Responsibility and Conduct reaffirmed a view on lawyers’ duty of confidentiality toward their clients in a recent advisory opinion. Specifically, the Committee reaffirmed past authority, which stated that attorneys may not disclose information that was learned via their representation of a client--particularly information that is embarrassing in nature. This extends to information that can technically be obtained elsewhere due to its public availability, if that information was disclosed to a client’s attorney in confidence.</p>
