            <p>Donald Trump’s election victory signals the potential for stark changes in US law in the coming months and years. A Trump presidency, along with a Republican-controlled Senate, almost certainly guarantees that President Obama’s choice of Judge Merrick Garland for the Supreme Court will not progress beyond his nomination. Beyond this open Supreme Court seat, the court’s oldest justices lean liberal, meaning that Trump’s power to shape the court may extend well beyond a single replacement for Antonin Scalia during his presidency.</p>
